Process: A unit of execution that has its own working space in the memory :)

Heap: The memory space allotted to a Java Application for use.
(Grows downward! :D)

Thread: A unit of execution within a process.
        They use the resources allotted to their respective parent process :)

Stack: Memory that threads have for their local variables and stuff :)
(Grows upward)

Concurrency: Application doing more than one thing at a time (generally, with the help of multiple threads).



